I0602 05:59:42.408056 1152912 input_loop.go:34] HandleUserInput called with text: "Cleanly offloadable now (different files, no shared state):\n    - Full-corpus labeling scale-up — run label.py (now solc_json-capable) across all 149k contracts as a background batch, emitting the full weak-label JSONL. Pure CPU, embarrassingly parallel, just\n    slow. Already in todo.md. \n    - Gold-label benchmark prep — fetch and normalize SmartBugs-Curated and SolidiFI into the same JSONL schema as our labels. This is the real held-out test set the solver must be evaluated on (never\n    trust Slither labels for eval). Independent fetch/parse work.\n    - Incident-DB ingestion — pull Rekt/Forta/SWC data into a structured table for the reward's class-prevalence term (ARCHITECTURE §5). Self-contained scraping/parsing.\n\n    Offloadable with a clear interface contract:\n    - More vuln-class generators — beyond the three now in generate.py (reentrancy, access-control, unchecked-return), classes like tx.origin auth, delegatecall injection, weak-prng, unprotected\n    selfdestruct. Each is a self-contained VulnGenerator subclass following the existing pattern; an agent can add one per task as long as it conforms to the sample(rng, variant) -> Challenge interface\n    and passes its own EVM-verify check.\n    - Difficulty/obfuscation knobs for the generator — more decoy functions, control-flow padding, renamed-variable noise — to make challenges non-trivial. Touches only generate.py's helpers.\n    - Real-corpus code grafting — embedding the vulnerable seam inside real mainnet contracts (the realism anchor) rather than synthesized shells. This is bigger and riskier (compile failures on\n    arbitrary contracts), genuinely separable, and high-value.\n\n    Infrastructure / housekeeping (good for a low-context agent):\n    - The git worktree setup you already assigned out.\n    - Declarative persistence of ~/.solc-select and .foundry via home-manager (in todo.md) so installs survive reboots.\n    - The gas-field parser fix in verify.py (the kind/Standard shape didn't match Foundry's JSON, so gas is None) — small, isolated.\n    - CI / smoke test — a tiny script that runs verify.py --demo and a 2-contract generate.py to catch regressions.\n    \n    Caveats on what to keep central, not offload:\n    - The solver itself (training loop, label-confidence stratification) and the adaptive curriculum/RLVR loop are the integrative core — they depend on everyone's outputs and embody the §0 invariant,\n    so they shouldn't be fanned out.\n    - Anything touching the EVM verifier's verdict logic stays central and frozen — it's the one component that must not drift.\n    - Watch the coordination hazard already noted: avoid git add -A from multiple agents in one tree; the worktree split fixes this.\n  \n    Highest-leverage offloads right now: full-corpus labeling, gold-benchmark prep, and additional vuln-class generators — those three unblock the solver and the eventual benchmark without colliding."
